Meet UPSers in a New Way

November 17, 2020
UPS Teams With Atlanta-Area Organizations To Give Old Uniforms New Life

Company is working with two local non-profit organizations to upcycle thousands of old uniforms into dog leashes, benefitting programs to provide much-needed homes and jobs for Atlanta-area residents - including some four-legged ones.

Read more on initiative
Open the link in a new window
November 09, 2020
Peak Surcharge Update

Updated Peak Surcharge information is now available for review, including Peak Surcharge rates for International shipments that will take effect beginning November 15, 2020.

Review a Detailed Listing of the Applicable Peak Surcharges.
Open the link in a new window
November 03, 2020
UPS Announces Changes To Board Of Directors

Company announced the election of Kate Johnson, President, Microsoft US, and Russell Stokes, President & CEO of GE Aviation Services and Chairman of GE Power Portfolio, to the UPS Board of Directors, effective immediately. In addition, UPS announced that John Stankey is leaving the board to focus on his responsibilities as CEO AT&T Inc.

Read more on announcement
Open the link in a new window
October 29, 2020
Preview the 2021 UPS Rates

Effective December 27, 2020, the rates for UPS® Ground, UPS Air and International services will increase an average of 4.9%. Rates for value-added services and other charges will also increase.

Read more and preview the 2021 Rate Changes
October 28, 2020
UPS Releases 3Q 2020 Earnings

Company announced third-quarter 2020 consolidated revenue of $21.2 billion, a 15.9% increase over the third quarter of 2019. Consolidated average daily volume increased 13.5% year over year. Net income was $2.0 billion for the quarter, 11.8% above the same period in 2019, or 10.7% on an adjusted basis.

Read more on earnings announcement
Open the link in a new window
October 27, 2020
UPS Aims To Sign Up 50,000 At ‘UPS Brown Friday’ Hiring Events Nationwide

One-day hiring blitz on October 30 is part of UPS’s larger effort to hire over 100,000 seasonal employees. Nearly 250 virtual and in-person job fairs will be held in company locations nationwide.

Read more on hiring event
Open the link in a new window
October 23, 2020
UPS Enables Global Launch Of New Apple Products

October 23 is launch day for the new iPhone and iPad, and UPS has worked for weeks to ensure that pre- ordered devices will be delivered to customers and retail stores as promised.

Read more on Apple shipments
Open the link in a new window
October 21, 2020
UPS CEO Carol B. Tomé Ranked No. 5 On Fortune’s 2020 Most Powerful Women In Business List

Carol recently was ranked by Fortune as the fifth most powerful woman in business. She was recognized for her goals to boost the company’s returns on investments it makes, increase efficiency and cut costs.

Read Fortune’s profile on Carol and an edited Q&A.;
Open the link in a new window
October 21, 2020
UPS’s Leadership In Corporate Citizenship Recognized Amid COVID-19 Pandemic

For the fifth consecutive year, UPS was named to Forbes and JUST Capital’s annual JUST 100 list for its commitment to serving its workers, customers, communities, the environment and shareholders. The company was again recognized as the industry leader in the transportation sector.

Read more on award
Open the link in a new window
September 25, 2020
UPS Announces New Environmental Commitment Supporting Underserved Communities Globally

The growing urgency of supporting environmental and social justice efforts around the world has fueled a new commitment by UPS to plant more than 50 million trees by 2030, in alignment with the United Nations Sustainable Development Goals period (2015-2030).

Read More on UPS Commitment
Open the link in a new window
September 24, 2020
UPS Appoints Nikki Clifton To Lead The UPS Foundation, Announces Retirement Of Ed Martinez After 44 Years Of Distinguished Service

Nicole “Nikki” Clifton will serve as President of Social Impact and The UPS Foundation, effective November 1, with the retirement of Eduardo “Ed” Martinez.

Read more on announcement
Open the link in a new window
September 14, 2020
The UPS Store Unveils New and Modern Store Design

Nation’s largest retail shipping chain reveals energetic concept to meet evolving consumer and small business owner needs in an e-commerce world.

Read more about new store design
September 14, 2020
Never Forget: UPSers Pay Tribute To 9/11 Heroes

To honor the nearly 3,000 lives lost on 9/11, UPSers around the world proudly took part in the fifth annual 9/11 Promise Run and Ride.

Read story
Open the link in a new window
September 11, 2020
UPS Appoints Eva Boratto And Wayne Hewett To Board Of Directors

Company announced the election of Eva Boratto, Chief Financial Officer and Executive Vice President of CVS Health and Wayne Hewett, former Chief Executive Officer of Klöckner Pentaplast Group and of Arysta LifeScience Corporation, to the UPS Board of Directors, effective immediately. 

Read more on announcement
Open the link in a new window
September 09, 2020
UPS To Hire Over 100,000 For Holiday Season

Flexible shifts, full- and part-time positions available at thousands of locations and over a third of past seasonal hires landed permanent jobs at UPS.

Read more on announcement
Open the link in a new window
September 02, 2020
UPS SurePost Services Increase

Effective October 18, 2020, rates for all UPS SurePost services will increase by $0.24. For greater detail, view detailed SurePost rates at the website referred to in your UPS SurePost service agreement.

Read more on UPS Rate Change Information announcements
August 26, 2020
UPS Announces Executive Leadership Team Changes

Company announces the appointment of Nando Cesarone to President, U.S. Operations and Scott Price to President, UPS International.

Read more on announcement
Open the link in a new window
August 21, 2020
UPS Expanding Kansas City Air Operations

It takes plenty of space to park a wide-body cargo jet, and UPS’s facility at Kansas City International Airport is getting a lot more of it. The facility, known as an air gateway, is being renovated and expanded. 

Learn How to Park a Wide-Body Cargo Jet
Open the link in a new window
August 18, 2020
The Logistics of Caring

UPS’s values have always driven our common purpose to help people in need anywhere, and everywhere, in any way that we can.

Learn more in the 2019 UPS Foundation Social Impact Report
Open the link in a new window
July 30, 2020
UPS Releases 2Q 2020 Earnings

Company announced second-quarter 2020 consolidated revenue increased to $20.5 billion, a 13.4% increase from the second quarter of 2019.  Net income was $1.8 billion for the quarter; adjusted net income was $1.9 billion, 8.8% above the same period in 2019.

Read more on earnings announcement
Open the link in a new window
July 28, 2020
UPS Promotes Laura Lane To Chief Corporate Affairs And Communications Officer

Lane will join UPS’s Executive Leadership Team and report directly to CEO Carol Tomé. She will oversee Public Policy and Government Affairs, Public Relations, Employee Communications, and the UPS Foundation.

Read more on announcement
Open the link in a new window
July 15, 2020
UPS Launches Saturday Standard Deliveries As Europe E-Commerce Sales Surge

New service available in eight leading e-commerce markets: the UK, Germany, France, Netherlands, Belgium, Italy, Spain and Poland.

Read more on new service
Open the link in a new window
July 13, 2020
UPS Names Angela Hwang To Board Of Directors

Angela Hwang is a member of Pfizer’s Executive Team and is Group President of the Pfizer Biopharmaceuticals Group.

Read more on announcement
Open the link in a new window
July 12, 2020
Updated UPS Rate Change Information

Effective July 12, 2020, the UPS Tariff/Terms and Conditions of Service and the 2020 UPS Rate and Services Guides have been updated.

Read more about the Rate Change
June 30, 2020
UPS Publishes 18th Annual Sustainability Report Highlighting Progress

Company announces launch of its 18th annual Sustainability Report, “Accelerating Sustainable Solutions.”

Read Current Sustainability Report
Open the link in a new window
June 24, 2020
UPS Commends Georgia Legislature On Passing Hate Crimes Bill

Company commends the Georgia Senate and House on approving bipartisan legislation that includes additional penalties and sentences for any crime motivated by a victim’s race, color, religion, national origin, sexual orientation, gender or physical ability.

Read press release
Open the link in a new window
June 19, 2020
Diversity in the Workplace

Kevin Warren, UPS Chief Marketing Officer, spoke to Bloomberg about diversity in the workplace.

Watch the interview
Open the link in a new window
June 12, 2020
UPS Giving $3.2 Million to Programs Supporting Racial Equality

Kevin Warren, UPS Chief Marketing Officer, spoke to CNN about how UPS plans to move the company and communities forward.

Watch the interview
Open the link in a new window
June 10, 2020
UPS Healthcare Continues Global Facility Expansion To Meet Growing Demands In Key Markets

Series of facility expansions to  healthcare-dedicated warehouse and distribution network in key global markets demonstrates UPS's commitment to  healthcare industry.

Read more on expansions
Open the link in a new window
June 08, 2020
UPS Calls for Justice and Reform to Advance Equality

UPS is stepping up its actions in support of justice, reform and equality for Black Americans in response to the killings of Ahmaud Arbery, George Floyd, Breonna Taylor and others.

Read about actions being taken 
Open the link in a new window
June 02, 2020
Demonstrations across the U.S.

UPS is carefully monitoring the ongoing demonstrations in numerous cities throughout the U.S. Our priority is the safety of our employees and our customers. Despite some delays, we are working to ensure that normal UPS service continues.

Read the Service Update
June 01, 2020
UPS To Mark World Environment Day By Matching Offsets Of Carbon Neutral Shipments In June

Company will commemorate World Environment Day on June 5 by matching the carbon offsets of all packages shipped via its carbon neutral program during the month of June.

Read more on program
Open the link in a new window
June 01, 2020
The UPS Foundation Commits US$3 Million To Gavi To Expand Innovative Last Mile Delivery Network ...

UPS alliance with Gavi builds on successful efforts to expand and improve vaccine delivery in Uganda and some of the world’s most underserved communities.

Read more on alliance
Open the link in a new window
May 28, 2020
UPS Healthcare Announces UPS® Premier

UPS Healthcare expands its healthcare capabilities with UPS Premier as part of ongoing service and technology upgrades to meet priority-handling needs of healthcare shipments. 

Read more on expansion
Open the link in a new window
May 18, 2020
UPS Delivers 5 Millionth Meal to Rural Students and Their Families Impacted by Novel Coronavirus Crisis

Collaborative ‘Emergency Meals-to-You’ Program Delivers on Promise to Provide Students with Heathy Food During Challenging Time

Read more on partnership
Open the link in a new window
May 18, 2020
UPS Healthcare Provides Urgent Support for Dr. Reddy’s Laboratories’ Temperature-Sensitive Medicines

Due to flight restrictions on the pharmaceutical company’s supply chain because of the Coronavirus pandemic, Dr. Reddy’s teamed up with UPS Healthcare to get 30 tons of temperature-controlled medical cargo from India to the U.S.

Read more on collaboration
Open the link in a new window
May 13, 2020
UPS To Launch Air Service From Gary/Chicago International Airport

Company will expand its express air network to Gary/Chicago International Airport. Service begins Nov. 2, in time for the peak holiday shipping season

Read more on service expansion
Open the link in a new window
May 04, 2020
UPS Supports Edwards Lifesciences’ Distribution Of Critical ICU Monitoring Equipment And Other Medical Technologies

Solutions and expertise deployed include UPS Temperature True® shipping services, air freight services and warehouse optimization.

Read more on UPS leveraging expertise
Open the link in a new window
April 29, 2020
UPS And Michaels Launch Contactless Curbside Pickup Of Packages And Return Drop-Offs At UPS Access Point Locations

UPS and Michaels offering consumers a safe and secure option to pick up packages and drop off returns outside of select Michaels stores across the United States

Read more on curbside service
Open the link in a new window
April 28, 2020
UPS Releases 1Q 2020 Earnings

UPS Expertise and Flexible Global Network Keep Supply Chains Moving

Read more on this quarter's report
Open the link in a new window
April 27, 2020
UPS Flight Forward, CVS To Launch Residential Drone Delivery Service In Florida Retirement Community To Assist In Coronavirus Response

Drones to deliver prescription medicines from a Florida CVS pharmacy for the largest retirement community in U.S.

Read more on service
Open the link in a new window
April 24, 2020
UPS Supporting NYC Healthcare Workers, First Responders & Community Organizations Amid Coronavirus Pandemic

Company backs several New York City community support efforts, including the donation of 5,000 masks to a health center in Red Hook; hand sanitizer and other supplies to NYPD; food for Henry Street Settlement and Vision Urbana, partnership to transport more than 1 million square yards of fabric to NYC for hospital gowns; and UPS Foundation funding to the United Way of New York City.

Read more on partnerships
Open the link in a new window
April 23, 2020
UPS Launches Smart Warehouse Technology

UPS Supply Chain Solutions launches warehouse network technology designed to make distribution centers smarter and more efficient.

Read more on new technology
Open the link in a new window
April 23, 2020
Updates to the UPS Tobacco/Vape Policy

Effective May 1, 2020, UPS will be updating the UPS Tobacco Policy that will impact existing and new vape customers.

Read More to preview the 2020 policy updates
Open the link in a new window
April 21, 2020
Virginia Center For Innovative Technology (CIT), UPS, DroneUp, And Workhorse Group Test Unmanned Systems For Coronavirus Response

Collaborators seek ways to support US Coronavirus response amid social distancing protocols.

Read more on testing
Open the link in a new window
April 20, 2020
UPS Supports Textile Producer SanMar By Shipping Over 1.7 Million Face Masks

UPS delivers more than 1.7 million face masks for San Mar, which has converted its clothing production facilities to support protective mask production.

Read more on partnership
Open the link in a new window
April 20, 2020
The UPS Foundation Allocates $15M to U.S. Community Organizations and Worldwide Non-Profits in Fight Against Coronavirus and to Support the Road to Recover

Funding directed to food security, healthcare, education and financial stability.

Read more on funding plans
Open the link in a new window
April 17, 2020
Keeping The American And Global Economy Moving

UPS Details Efforts to Fight COVID-19 and Enhance its Unmatched Network to Power Customers’ Supply Chains to Deliver Needed Goods and Services to Save Lives.

Read more on UPS efforts
Open the link in a new window
April 17, 2020
UPS Adds Over 200 Flights In April To Support Project Airbridge Coronavirus Relief Efforts

Company has added over 200 company-owned and chartered air freighter flights in April to support FEMA’s Project Airbridge and other healthcare-related missions. 

Read more on flights
